<dl id="n56124e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56124e">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56124e"> 124(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> blood, musk <font color="green">[&amp;]</font> / hashisch <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n56124e"><li>FW 359.09 </li><li><a href="../../flex/mf/lexmf.htm#n56124e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/mf/l39mf.htm#n56124e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n56124e">MS BL 47480.248v</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:382 <a name="mfd5" href="../../ff/fdra/mda.htm#mfd5">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/mf/mfd5.htm#n56124e">Draft: II.3&sect;6.5</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">All the splendour and squalor, the beauty and baseness, the glamour and grotesqueness, the magic and the mournfulness, the bravery and the baseness of Oriental life are here: its picture of the three great Arab passions, love, war and fancy, entitle it to be called &ldquo;<mark>Blood, Musk and Hashish</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE4" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE4"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 157</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
